original: Johanson, Nils Gottfrid, istads-inigenjör, Strömstad, f. 20/8/90i i Sund|svall av byggmäst. Nils Magnus J. o. h. h. f. Källström. G. 24 m. Signe Holm. Barn: Inga f. _ 25, stud., Olde 29, stud. — Ing:ex. i Örebro 15. Anst. inom byggn rbranscben h. fadern samt s. mätn :tekn. h. firma Eggert & Sandström i Sthlm 09-12, bitr. stads-ing. i Lidköp. 15-17, sitadsing. i Strömstad sed. 17. Medl. av Odd Fellow.
translated: Johanson, Nils Gottfrid, civil engineer, from Strömstad, born August 20th, 1890 in Sundsvall to builder Nils Magnus J. and his wife Källström. Married to Signe Holm since 1924. Children: Inga, born [unknown date], studying; Olde, born 1929, studying. Graduated from Örebro Technical School in 1915. Worked in the construction industry with his father and as a surveying technician at the firm Eggert & Sandström in Stockholm from 1909-1912, assistant city engineer in Lidköping from 1915-1917, and city engineer in Strömstad since 1917. Member of Odd Fellow.
